\n< Serena >Cheers.
\n< Erika >Cheers.
\n< Serena >.......
\n< Erika >...phew.
\n< Erika >Hahaha~! So this is the sweet taste of victory!

\n< Erika >When I fought against the Minotaur, I had to
be hospitalized immediately, so I
couldn't even have a sip of alcohol.

\n< Serena >To think you want to celebrate that time
again. You're still a strange person.

\n< Erika >Serena, you can really hold your liquor. Have
you also learned the taste of alcohol in
that town over there?
\n< Erika >Well, time for another drink...

\n< Serena >Erika-dono, you are with child. It may not
be wise to drink too much...

\n< Erika >Ah... I see. Alcohol is bad for the baby in
my belly... was it?
\n< Serena >That belly...

\n< Erika >Well, I haven't slept with any other men
before or after that
.I guess some of their seed hit me.

\n< Erika >I was also seriously injured and couldn't
have an abortion. Before I knew it, I
ended up with this belly.

\n< Erika >Well, in this situation, I have no choice but
to give birth. Even if it's a child
conceived through rape, I have no choice
but to give birth.
\n< Erika >Well, it doesn't matter to me.

\n< Erika >But more importantly, Serena, you can
really hold your liquor. Have you also
learned the taste of alcohol in that
town over there?

\n< Serena >Well, I've never thought it was delicious,
but now, a little...

\n< Serena >No, it still tastes weird. It tickles my
nose a bit.

\n< Erika >Hahaha. That's fine. If you keep drinking like
this since your a child, you'll end up
becoming a heavy drinker like me.

\n< Serena >If I can become like Erika-dono, maybe I
should try a little harder to enjoy
alcohol.

\n< Erika >M-Me? Nah, my body is all beaten up and
nothing is going well for me. There's
really nothing good about aiming for
someone like me. Seriously, seriously...

\n< Serena >That's not true... I respect you. Even in this
moment, my respect for you grows
stronger.

\n< Serena >Castellum. In that town, I witnessed a lot of
evil. I saw how even a little kindness
can reveal the weakness of people's
hearts.
\n< Serena >...That's why I'm surprised right now.

\n< Serena >The way Erika-dono carries herself, her
behavior... Your strength. Just how
incredible it is.
\n< Serena >Can I behave like you, from now on...?
\n< Erika >Splendore-chan was amazing, right?

\n< Serena >Yeah, I found them. I had a little trouble,
but while I was there,
Marilou-dono took care of me.

\n< Serena >Not a scratch.
I'm really glad...really ........

\n< Erika >Well then, this is the grand finale. It's a
happy ending, isn't it?

\n< Serena >Well, that's true.
But it depends on what my
father, mother, and older sister have to
say...

\n< Serena >I'm just worried about what kind of
punishment awaits me.
\n< Erika >Oh, oh, come here and squeeze me tightly.

\n< Erika >Ahh, I'm really glad. I was worried every
day when i was bedridden.
\n< Erika >I'm really glad that nothing happened...
\n< Serena >T-to the point of crying...

\n< Erika >No, you see, Serena. You don't understand,
you don't understand. How worried I am
about you, how much I worry.

\n< Erika >I kept wondering how
Serena was doing now,
if she's eating properly, if she found a
place to stay, if she hasn't been
deceived by some bad guy, if she hasn't
gotten involved in something bad...

\n< Erika >On the hospital bed. That kind of scene
keeps popping up in my mind,
disappearing, and then reappearing, and
every time it does, my chest tightens.

\n< Erika >Even I'm like this.
I can't stop thinking about how your parents feel.
It makes my heart go gwawa wah~~. ......
\n< Serena >Hmm...

\n< Erika >So, go and get scolded for real. It's
Serena's duty and responsibility. That's
how it is.
\n< Serena >Hmm...

\n< Erika >...It's a happy thing to have a family that
worries about you. I grew up in an
orphanage, so I don't know what my mom
looks like.

\n< Serena >Is that so? I remember, Erika-sama ran
away from home before.

\n< Erika >Did I say something like that?
You have a good memory, huh?

\n< Erika >...Well,
running away from home means left the orphanage and was on my own.
I didn't want to be a nun.

\n< Erika >Come to think of it, at first, I was
planning to search for my mom.  I
had no clues, all I knew was her hair
color.
\n< Serena >Speaking of which.

\n< Erika >I'm really persistent.
So it's fine, but...

\n< Erika >Well, when I was abandoned at the orphanage,
it seems like my mom gave me a charm to
protect me.

\n< Erika >It's woven with hair. I think it's
probably my mom's hair.

\n< Erika >It's a bit more reddish than mine... Like a
wine red... I wonder what kind of person
she was...
\n< Erika >Huh?

\n< Serena >Adventurers, huh? I should have put up the Closed
sign... Geez, they always come at the
worst times.

\n< Erika >There's also the possibility that the Master
forgot their key or something.
\n< Serena >...Oh well...
\n< Erika >Hi there. Yo...

\n< Serena >No, Erika, please sit down.
I'll take it for here.
\n< Erika >Serena is also burdened with by my troubles, huh...
\n< Erika >Ah... Is that so? Sorry, I appreciate it.

\n<  >Oh, wow! I-I-I'm sorry!!!
\n< Serena >It hurts...
\n<  >Are you okay? Can you stand up?

\n< Serena >...WWell, I only hit my face and butt.
It's not a big deal...

\n<  >I'm sorry... I've always been a bit clumsy,
or rather, carefree...
\n< Serena >.......
\n<  >Ah... um, well, that, that...
\n<  >Right! So, for now! Hello!!
\n<  >I'm an Aspiring adventurer!

\n< Erika >Cheers.

\n< Erika >...phew.

\n< Erika >When I fought against the Minotaur, I had to

\n< Erika >Ah... I see. Alcohol is bad for the baby in

\n< Erika >I was also seriously injured and couldn't

\n< Erika >Well, it's fine with me.

\n< Erika >But more importantly, Serena, you can
really hold your liquor. Have you also

\n< Serena >Well, I've never thought it was delicious,

\n< Serena >No, it still tastes weird. It tickles my

\n< Serena >If I can become like Erika-dono, maybe I
should try a little harder to enjoy
alcohol.

\n< Erika >M-Me? Nah, my body is all beaten up and
nothing is going well for me. There's
really nothing good about aiming for
someone like me. Seriously, seriously...

\n< Serena >My body is also in a terrible state. And
my belly is in this condition too...

\n< Serena >My body is also in a terrible state. From
the outside, all you can see is this
bandage... but on the inside, it's
equally damaged.
\n< Serena >...That's why I'm surprised right now.

\n< Serena >Erika-sama, your appearance, your behavior... Your
strength. Just how incredible it is.
\n< Serena >Can I behave like you, from now on...?
\n< Erika >Splendore-chan was amazing, right?

\n< Serena >Yeah, I found them. I had a little trouble,
but while I was there,
Marilou-dono took care of me.
\n< Serena >Although I managed to get here from the eastern city... it seems that being with me now was quite a burden on Splendor.

\n< Serena >Splendor seems to be at ease when
it is near Marilou's daughter.

\n< Serena >This belly... When I showed it, she was crying
... and was surprised .
\n< Erika >...What are you planning to do from now on?

\n< Serena >I will wait here for the pick-up from
Gratzia. Since I sent a message, they
should come directly.

\n< Serena >However, it became a big deal... There are too
many things that happened.

\n< Serena >Castorum is in a state of chaos right now. I
came out as if running away... What I
did there, what I did there...

\n< Serena >Depending on the situation, it could become a
problem. At the very least, my father
will likely be implicated.

\n< Serena >Before the problem surfaces, if I could be put
into some monastery or something, it
would be a perfect resolution.

\n< Serena >But it will only burden my older sister even
more.
\n< Erika >Is that really okay, Serena?

\n< Erika >Serena, are you really willing to risk
everything and sacrifice your future for
that? Is the outcome going to be a
lifetime of confinement in a monastery?

\n< Erika >After going that far to help Splendore-chan,
you won't be able to be friends with her
anymore, right?
\n< Erika >...I can't accept that.
\n< Serena >Yeah... you're right...

\n< Serena >It wasn't necessarily the outcome I had
hoped for, but...
\n< Serena >I agree... but...

\n< Erika >Hey, let's run away right now! It's fine,
isn't it? After all, you'll just end up
being thrown into a monastery, right?

\n< Erika >If that's the case, then let's leave this
troublesome house behind!... That's
right! Let's become adventurers
together!

\n< Erika >Well, there may be plenty of hardships, but
you know what? It's all about freedom!
You get to experience both joy and
sadness, and it's all yours!

\n< Erika >I know what i look like saying this
with a big belly and weak arms, but...
at least adventurers are free! Happiness
and sadness, it's all yours!

\n< Erika >Your life is your own, right?!
Who has something to say about it?!
\n< Serena >.......
\n< Serena >...Honestly, you are so selfish and pushy...

\n< Serena >And you are a considerate and sincere
person.

\n< Serena >From the first time you spoke to me until
now, you have always been considerate of
me.

\n< Serena >But it's no good. I am a noble. I am the
executor of justice and responsibility.

\n< Serena >...In order to save Splendore... I sacrificed
many things that I possessed.

\n< Serena >Each time I lost something,
I realized how big and heavy it is.
Can something sosignificant come solely from within me?

\n< Serena >...I thought.
Erika-dono was right. Marilou was right.

\n< Serena >I was built upon the love and kindness of
not just my parents... but even more
people than that.

\n< Serena >I wonder how much time and effort has
been spent to shape me as I am now.
\n< Serena >How much love has been poured into me?

\n< Serena >I, with my selfishness, have damaged that
version of myself.

\n< Serena >The love that I should have returned to the
people I love... I have selfishly
damaged it.

\n< Serena >I must accept that punishment. If I were
to run away from responsibility and
sin... I would become just like the many
adults who have tormented me.
\n< Serena >That is just unbearable...

\n< Erika >Wait, Serena, that's not the conclusion.
Why does it have to be like that?

\n< Erika >No one wants that from you. That kind of
thing...
\n< Serena >It is what I desire for myself.

\n< Serena >Looking at Erika-dono, I thought that once
again.

\n< Serena >You didn't run away from your
responsibilities.

\n< Serena >The pain and hardships of those results.
You're bear them all without even
complaining to me once.

\n< Serena >All the words that come out of your mouth
are words of concern for me... I thought
it was amazing. Thinking
someone was so strong.

\n< Serena >Now, bearing the same pain, that's why I
strongly feel it. I want to become like
you too.
\n< Erika >No, no. I'm not like that... I am...

\n< Serena >Thank you, Erika-dono. Thanks to you, my
heart is now brighter than ever before.

\n< Serena >I will write you letters.

\n< Serena >It might become boring with things like
what I've been thinking about each day
or what I've been reading.
\n< Serena >I would be happy if you read it.

\n< Serena >...I'm going to step outside for a bit to get
some fresh air.

\n< Serena >I probably won't come to this town
anymore.
I want to see and remember it well..

\n<  >I'm sorry... It wouldn't open easily, so I,
um, forcefully... went like, Gah!
\n< Serena >...The door should have been locked...
\n<  >Eh, r-really!?

\n<  >Oh no...Well then...
I might have... broken...
\n< Serena >.......
\n<  >Ahh... um, well, uh...
